# Nelumbo HTTP server — example requests
#
# Start the server first (loads the fibonacci example into the knowledge base):
#
#   ./gradlew :website:serverJar
#   java -jar http/build/libs/nelumbo-http-server-*.jar \
#        src/main/resources/org/modelingvalue/nelumbo/examples/fibonacci.nl
#
# Then run the requests below (IntelliJ HTTP Client / VS Code REST Client).
#
# Note: a posted document is self-contained — it declares the variables it queries
# with (e.g. `Integer r`). The loaded files provide the types/functors/rules/facts.

@host = http://localhost:9000

### Liveness check
GET {{host}}/health

### Knowledge base metadata (types, counts, loaded files)
GET {{host}}/metadata

### Solve an existential query — expect status "true", bindings r=55
POST {{host}}/eval
Content-Type: text/plain

Integer r
fib(10)=r ?

### Ground query that holds — expect status "true"
POST {{host}}/eval
Content-Type: text/plain

fib(5)=5 ?

### Ground query that is refuted — expect status "false"
POST {{host}}/eval
Content-Type: text/plain

fib(5)=6 ?

### Multiple queries in one document — both evaluated, results returned in order
POST {{host}}/eval
Content-Type: text/plain

Integer a, b
fib(7)=a ?
fib(12)=b ?

### Traced evaluation — currently stubbed: trace=null, traceStatus="not-implemented"
POST {{host}}/eval/trace
Content-Type: text/plain

Integer r
fib(8)=r ?

### Syntax error — expect HTTP 400 with an errors[] entry carrying line/column/message
POST {{host}}/eval
Content-Type: text/plain

fib(

### Empty body — expect HTTP 400
POST {{host}}/eval
Content-Type: text/plain


### JSON envelope — document plus options in the body instead of the path
POST {{host}}/eval
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "document": "Integer r\nfib(10)=r ?\n"
}

### JSON envelope with trace flag — enables tracing on /eval (stubbed for now)
POST {{host}}/eval
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "document": "Integer r\nfib(10)=r ?\n",
  "trace": true
}

### JSON envelope with limit — cap bindings per query; adds "truncated": true when applied
### (most useful against a knowledge base whose queries have many solutions)
POST {{host}}/eval
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "document": "Integer r\nfib(10)=r ?\n",
  "limit": 1
}
